MAPPING.DESCRIPTION: This mapping loads date to create an easy-to-use lookup table for "date range by offset" (for use by other ETLS)
MAPPING.NAME: m_FCST_FIS_OFFSET_DATES

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: Lookup on DAY_DIMENSION to fetch required field values.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: LKP_DAY_DIMENSION

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Sql Query
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: with data as ( SELECT to_number( cy_year_yyyy ) fiscal_year ,to_number(CY_MONTH_NUM) fiscal_period ,to_number(CY_WK_OF_YEAR) fiscal_week ,day_date FROM DAY_DIMENSION ), ranked_data as ( select fiscal_year ,fiscal_period ,fiscal_week ,day_date ,dense_rank() over (order by fiscal_year,fiscal_week) week_rank ,dense_rank() over (order by fiscal_year,fiscal_period) period_rank ,dense_rank() over (order by fiscal_year) year_rank from data ), current_rank as ( select week_rank, period_rank ,year_rank from ranked_data where day_date = trunc(sysdate) ), all_data as ( select 'week' as rcd_type ,r.week_rank - c.week_rank as offset_value ,min(r.day_date) as start_date ,max(r.day_date) as end_date from ranked_data r, current_rank c group by r.week_rank,c.week_rank union all select 'period' as rcd_type ,r.period_rank - c.period_rank as offset_value ,min(r.day_date) as start_date ,max(r.day_date) as end_date from ranked_data r, current_rank c group by r.period_rank,c.period_rank union all select 'year' as rcd_type ,r.year_rank - c.year_rank as offset_value ,min(r.day_date) as start_date ,max(r.day_date) as end_date from ranked_data r, current_rank c group by r.year_rank,c.year_rank order by rcd_type, offset_value ) select rcd_type,offset_value,start_date,end_date from all_data

INSTANCE.NAME: LKP_DAY_DIMENSION
